comment: It's  too complicated for those of us not born in the electronic age. You need to be able to control background noise without having to set it up for every situation. It takes too long naming the setting etc.

author: Kathy White
comment: I could not follow the instructions

author: camille walker
comment: As an app it functions well.  There are limitations for Android users on the hearing aids themselves that should be pointed out by the providers when we purchase Starkey hearing aids.  Apple has the market on streaming audio and media on these HAs because they have put the development in and made it proprietary. 😕 As a faithful android user with hearing loss, it really sucks. But the app works and functions properly.  So there is that.

I have a halo and streaming doesn't work. I used to have an iPhone but tree system was not right for me. Ive always had android/ Samsung devices I shouldn't be forced to by a $800 phone just to stream to my hearing aids. Please make this available. Thank you.
